cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of multi-organ segmentation in CT scans. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a shape-prior learning approach, which involves training a model to learn the geometric properties of each organ. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed solution on a public dataset, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-category of computer systems and networking, such as cs.MS (Computer Systems and Networking). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of multimedia, such as cs.MM (Multimedia).
